<h1>Problem 1944 - 2023 IMOSL, C2</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Determine the maximal length \(L\) of a sequence \(a_1,\dots,a_L\) of positive integers satisfying both the following properties:
every term in the sequence is less than or equal to \(2^{2023}\), and
there does not exist a consecutive subsequence \(a_i,a_{i+1},\dots,a_j\) (where \(1\le i\le j\le L\)) with a choice of signs \(s_i,s_{i+1},\dots,s_j\in\{1,-1\}\) for which\[s_ia_i+s_{i+1}a_{i+1}+\dots+s_ja_j=0.\]</p>
